Sentencas: An efficient steam electrolysis process for hydrogen production via a solid oxide electrolysis cell using porous network-like strontium doped lanthanum manganite (LSM)-yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) as the oxygen electrode material has been demonstrated.
Titulo: High temperature solid oxide electrolysis cell employing porous structured (La0.75Sr0.25)0.95MnO3 with enhanced oxygen electrode performance

Sentencas: The porous network-like LSM powder was prepared by a nitrate-glycine combustion method.
Titulo: High temperature solid oxide electrolysis cell employing porous structured (La0.75Sr0.25)0.95MnO3 with enhanced oxygen electrode performance

Sentencas: Impedance spectra and voltage-current density curves were measured as a function of cell current density and absolute humidity at 800 degrees C and 900 degrees C to characterize the cell performance.
Titulo: High temperature solid oxide electrolysis cell employing porous structured (La0.75Sr0.25)0.95MnO3 with enhanced oxygen electrode performance

Sentencas: The cell area specific resistance (ASR) was 0.26 Omega cm(2) at 900 degrees C with 0.5 A/cm(2) current density and 50% absolute humidity (AH).
Titulo: High temperature solid oxide electrolysis cell employing porous structured (La0.75Sr0.25)0.95MnO3 with enhanced oxygen electrode performance

Sentencas: The hydrogen production rate calculated from the Faraday's law was 362 ml/cm(2) h at 900 degrees C with 80 vol.% AH.
Titulo: High temperature solid oxide electrolysis cell employing porous structured (La0.75Sr0.25)0.95MnO3 with enhanced oxygen electrode performance

Sentencas: The cell performance results indicate that the porous network-like LSM-YSZ is a promising oxygen electrode for high temperature electrolysis cells.
Titulo: High temperature solid oxide electrolysis cell employing porous structured (La0.75Sr0.25)0.95MnO3 with enhanced oxygen electrode performance
